  "text": "These studies have borne out the predictions of the chemiosmotic hypothesis for auxin transport, but they have not addressed the central Cholodny-Went idea that tropic stimuli evoke a transverse cellular polarisation with respect to auxin transport. Indeed, it is not clear that PIN proteins are part of the proposed lateral auxin transport mechanism, nor that their activity or distribution is altered to achieve lateral auxin transport. A new study [CITATION_1] has now provided some clues to the link between gravity perception and auxin transport in stems and roots.",
